cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with monocular depth estimation using deep learning models. The use of self-supervised learning and knowledge distillation also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The fact that the proposed method is evaluated on the KITTI benchmark, which is a dataset for autonomous driving, suggests that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the use of image synthesis and reconstruction techniques suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category.
